3)Containerization and deployment in Minikube
Task-----
Expected Output:4 running containers of the image in Minikube cluster



Step-by-Step: Deploy Docker Hub Image in Minikube
1. Start Minikube with Docker driver
bash:
minikube start --driver=docker

2. Verify Docker is running
bash:
docker info

Look for Server Version and Running: true.
3. Create a Kubernetes Deployment
This example uses the nginx image from Docker Hub:
kubectl create deployment my-nginx --image=nginx



. Scale the deployment to
4 replicas
kubectl scale deployment my-nginx --replicas=4

5. Verify the pods are running
kubectl get pods
You should see 4 pods with names like my-nginx-xxxxxx in Running state.

ou should see 4 pods with names like my-nginx-xxxxxx in Running state.
6. (Optional) Expose the deployment
kubectl expose deployment my-nginx --type=NodePort --port=80
minikube service my-nginx




 Expected Output for Your Task
Task: 4 running containers of the image in Minikube cluster
Command to verify:
kubectl get pods


Expected Output:
NAME                         READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE
my-nginx-xxxxx               1/1     Running   0          1m
my-nginx-yyyyy               1/1     Running   0          1m
my-nginx-zzzzz               1/1     Running   0          1m
my-nginx-aaaaa               1/1     Running   0          1m





