Q4)Integrating Webhooks for CI/CD Automation
Task-----
Expected Output:
Jenkins Pipeline triggered automatically via GitHub Webhook without manual or SCM polling


Create Jenkinsfile in GitHub repo/
node {
    properties([
        pipelineTriggers([
            [$class: 'GitHubPushTrigger']
        ])
    ])

    stage('Build') {
        bat 'mvn clean install'
    }

    stage('Test') {
        bat 'mvn test'
    }

    stage('Deploy') {
        bat 'echo Deployment Completed'
    }
}
Commit & Push to GitHub.
Create a new Pipeline Job in Jenkins

STEP 3: Configure Jenkins to use your Jenkinsfile (from GitHub)

Inside the job:

Scroll to Pipeline section:

Definition: Pipeline script from SCM

SCM: Git

Repository URL: your GitHub repo URL

STEP 4: Enable the webhook trigger

Scroll up to Build Triggers:

✔ Check → GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling

This is important!

ngrok http 8080
https://abcd1234.ngrok-free.app/github-webhook/
Go to GitHub:

Your Repo → Settings → Webhooks → Add Webhook

Fill:

Field	Value
Payload URL	http://<jenkins-url>/github-webhook/
Content Type	application/json
Event	Just the push event
Secret	leave empty

Now go to your repo → make a small change → push.

Example:

git commit -m "webhook test"
git push
